# SEO/GEO Tool Rules

- Ship only features that help onboard a real site, read an audit, or execute prioritized fixes.
- Prefer deterministic rules, stored state, and explainable scoring.
- Do not add AI-generated ranking or copy unless explicitly approved.
- Keep changes small, reversible, and aligned with the current architecture.
- If a feature does not improve onboarding, audit clarity, or execution speed, do not build it.
- When implementing a milestone, stop after the smallest useful version is done.
- Ask for confirmation before major refactors or schema changes.
